Comparison between JSON VS XML
JSON
•	JSON is simple to read and write
•	It also supports array
•	Json files are more human-readable than xml
•	It supports only text and number data type

XML
•	XML is less simple as compared JSON
•	It doesn’t support array
•	XML files are less human readable
•	It supports many data types such as text, number, images, charts, graphs, etc.

Capture and Validate JSON Path

JSONPath:  It is a query language (like XPath for XML) used to find and extract specific data from JSON.

JSON Path Finder: It is a tool or web app that automatically generates those paths for you by visualizing the structure.


https://jsonpathfinder.com/ ---> User this link to find the path it will auto generate the path

https://jsonpath.com/ ---> user this link if you want to find the path

Example : 
{ 
  "students" : [
    {
			"sid" : 101,
			"sname": "Rohit",
			"grade": "A"
		},
		{
			"sid":102,
			"sname":"Mukund",
			"grade":"B"
		},
		{
			"sid":103,
			"sname":"Anirudh",
			"grade":"C"
		}
	]
}

Here the array will be student
And the path will be object 0, object 1, object 2
In array object always start with 0, 1, 2
And value will be 101, Rohit , A

So, our JSONPath will be

Student[0].sname     it will return Rohit
